# Example env for admin (Vite)
# Socket.IO server URL the admin SPA should connect to.
# Must include protocol (http:// or https://) and optional port.
# If omitted, the client falls back to the same origin as the page.
VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://localhost:5000

# Usage (development):
# "nix-shell --run "cd admin && VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://localhost:5000 npm run dev""

# Usage (build):
# nix-shell --run "cd admin && VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://my-server.example.com npm run build"

# Notes:
# - Vite exposes env variables prefixed with VITE_ to client code.
# - Do NOT commit secrets or production-only tokens to this file; use your CI/deploy env instead.
# - Admin authentication is username/password based (see /admin/api/auth/login); the
#   resulting JWT is sent in the Socket.IO handshake. There is no devicekey bypass.
